Privacy Policy for EdUnited

Effective Date: 15 January, 2025

At EdUnited, we respect your privacy and are committed to safeguarding any information you share with us while using our mobile application ("the App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when you use EdUnited to access study materials like quantum and college notes.

By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.

1. Information We Collect
Since EdUnited does not require user sign-up or account creation, the only information we may collect includes:

Usage Data:

We may automatically collect certain data when you use the App, such as the study materials you access, the time spent on each section, and other usage statistics. This helps us understand how users interact with the App and allows us to improve the content and functionality.
Device Information:

We may collect basic information about the device you use to access the App, such as the device type, operating system, version, unique device identifiers, and other technical data to help us optimize the App for your device.
Location Data (if applicable):

If the App uses location-based features (e.g., providing localized content), we may collect location data to enhance the experience. We will request your consent before collecting location information and you can choose to disable location tracking at any time via your device settings.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies:

We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your experience within the App, such as remembering your preferences or analyzing app usage patterns. You can manage cookie settings through your device settings.
2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used for the following purposes:

To operate and maintain the functionality of the App
To improve the Appâ€™s content and performance based on usage patterns
To provide location-based or personalized study material recommendations, if applicable
To analyze trends and app performance to enhance user experience
3. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell, rent, or lease your personal data to third parties. However, we may share data in the following situations:

Service Providers: We may share anonymous usage data with third-party service providers to help us analyze app performance, track app usage, or improve the service. These service providers are required to protect your data and use it only for the services they provide to us.

Legal Compliance: We may disclose information if required by law, such as in response to a subpoena, court order, or legal request from government authorities.

4. Data Retention
Since EdUnited does not require user accounts or store personal information, the data we collect (such as usage and device data) is retained only as long as necessary to improve the functionality of the App. If you want us to delete any data related to your use of the App, please contact us at [Your Contact Email].

5. Security of Your Information
We take reasonable steps to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, or disclosure. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the Internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

6. Your Rights and Choices
Since we do not collect personal information, the data we do collect is limited to usage data, device information, and location data (if enabled). However, you have the following choices:

Location Data: If you have consented to location-based services, you can disable location tracking through your device settings at any time.
Cookies: You can manage cookie preferences or disable them via your device or browser settings.
If you have any concerns or questions about the data we collect, please contact us at [Your Contact Email].

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page, with the "Effective Date" at the top. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we protect your data.

